      Updates and appointment table view with the given table, columns, and data.

      LAMBDA: Using lambda expressions in this code makes the code more concise and easier to read by encapsulating the logic of setting the start time column's cell value in a single line of code. The lambda expression acts as a "factory" to create the cell value property and set its value, which reduces the need for boilerplate code and makes the intent of the code clearer.

      Parameters:
      table - the table view to be updated
      idColumn - the column for appointment IDs
      userColumn - the column for user IDs@param customerIdColumn the column for customer IDs
      titleColumn - the column for appointment titles
      descriptionColumn - the column for appointment descriptions
      locationColumn - the column for appointment locations
      contactColumn - the column for appointment contacts
      typeColumn - the column for appointment types
      startColumn - the column for appointment start times
      endColumn - the column for appointment end times
      appList - the list of appointment data to populate the table view with
